WEBVTT

00:20.806 --> 00:24.350
[eclectic orchestral theme plays]

02:08.788 --> 02:13.085
It was the same woman from my dream,
I'm sure of it. The same face.

02:13.168 --> 02:16.713
You gotta stop watching all those
cop shows. They will mess you up.

02:16.796 --> 02:19.716
I feel like I know her,
I just don't remember from where.

02:19.799 --> 02:22.343
- Maybe someone from your criminal past.
- [scoffs]

02:22.427 --> 02:25.305
- I wasn't a criminal.
- No. Activist.

02:25.430 --> 02:26.765
Hacktivist.

02:27.557 --> 02:29.851
- Reformed, paroled, legal.
- Uh-huh.

02:29.935 --> 02:33.230
And what about all these
security companies that you hack for?

02:33.313 --> 02:35.857
Well, it's not hacking
if you get paid for it.

02:35.941 --> 02:38.818
Anyway, I thought I knew her
from one of my client companies,

02:38.944 --> 02:40.612
but no, that's not it.

02:40.695 --> 02:42.697
You've led a lot of different lives.

02:42.781 --> 02:44.032
- So have you.
- Me?

02:44.116 --> 02:46.701
I've been working at the same bookstore
since you met me,

02:46.785 --> 02:49.454
but not for much longer
if I don't shake my ass.

02:49.537 --> 02:52.373
- Oh... Wait, wait.
- [chuckles]

03:01.925 --> 03:05.345
OK, but tell me honestly,
am I sounding crazy?

03:06.346 --> 03:08.098
Maybe you should write about it.

03:09.099 --> 03:10.267
I am.

03:10.350 --> 03:14.020
Well, it is that time of year.
You always go a little crazy at Pride.

03:14.104 --> 03:15.772
You know why.

03:15.855 --> 03:19.109
Honey, if I had your parents,
I'd be more than a little crazy.

03:19.192 --> 03:21.778
- I'd be homicidal.
- Mm.

03:26.158 --> 03:28.827
[Deshawn] You got a funny look
in your eye, Will.

03:28.910 --> 03:30.703
You hot for me or somethin'?

03:30.787 --> 03:32.455
I know I'm USDA prime cut,

03:32.538 --> 03:34.457
but you should know
I don't swing that way.

03:35.583 --> 03:37.543
Thanks for clearing that up.

03:38.920 --> 03:41.965
Ain't gonna be good for my rep
having no 5-0 sittin' bedside.

03:42.048 --> 03:44.343
Yeah, it's not helping me much either.

03:44.425 --> 03:46.803
So you think you own me now
or somethin'?

03:46.886 --> 03:47.887
No...

03:49.264 --> 03:51.557
What I did for you
I would've done for anybody.

03:51.641 --> 03:53.768
So what, then?

03:56.855 --> 03:59.440
I was just thinking about
what you said in the car...

04:00.525 --> 04:02.235
about your dad being shot.

04:03.569 --> 04:05.322
Long time ago.

04:05.405 --> 04:07.032
Things ain't no different.

04:08.033 --> 04:09.284
My dad was shot.

04:10.702 --> 04:11.661
Dead?

04:13.538 --> 04:17.376
Some parts of him.
Finished his career.

04:19.252 --> 04:22.588
Cops get shot,
hear about it on the news all day.

04:22.672 --> 04:26.301
We get shot all the time,
but we don't mean nothin' to nobody.

04:29.762 --> 04:33.183
Will, tell me about your gangsta days.

04:37.062 --> 04:39.856
My kid? My fuckin' kid?

04:39.939 --> 04:41.358
What are you thinking?

04:41.441 --> 04:43.943
- Shoplifting, for Chrissakes?
- [boy panting]

04:44.027 --> 04:46.571
You know who I am? Do you?

04:47.655 --> 04:49.157
The matter with you?

04:51.534 --> 04:53.119
[sighs] I'm sorry.

05:03.380 --> 05:05.424
I don't know what he's thinkin'.

05:12.347 --> 05:15.392
Hey! Hey!

05:16.893 --> 05:19.562
This fuckin' kid.

05:19.645 --> 05:21.647
You picked the lock? [chuckles]

05:21.731 --> 05:24.401
My dad was always workin'.
I was always waitin'.

05:24.484 --> 05:26.861
Not much else to play with
at a police station.

05:26.945 --> 05:29.239
Yeah, Will, you know
you gotta teach me that trick.

05:29.322 --> 05:32.200
[chuckles] All right.

05:33.326 --> 05:34.702
I should go.

05:36.788 --> 05:38.164
[Deshawn] Hey.

05:38.248 --> 05:40.583
I don't owe you for what you did...

05:41.418 --> 05:44.670
but you should know
I won't ever forget it.

05:49.842 --> 05:53.472
[Nomi] I've been thinking about my life,

05:53.554 --> 05:56.682
and all of the mistakes that I've made.

06:02.230 --> 06:05.775
The ones that stay with me,
the ones that I regret,

06:05.858 --> 06:08.528
are the ones that I made
because of fear.

06:18.788 --> 06:22.041
For a long time,
I was afraid to be who I am

06:22.125 --> 06:24.503
because I was taught by my parents

06:24.585 --> 06:28.923
that there's something wrong
with someone like me.

06:29.799 --> 06:34.513
Something offensive,
something you would avoid,

06:34.595 --> 06:36.473
maybe even pity.

06:37.640 --> 06:40.393
Something that you could never love.

06:40.477 --> 06:43.062
[singing softly]

06:45.731 --> 06:48.651
My mom, she's a fan
of St. Thomas Aquinas.

06:48.734 --> 06:51.488
She calls pride a sin.

06:51.571 --> 06:54.449
And of all the venal and mortal sins,

06:54.533 --> 06:58.244
St. Thomas saw pride
as the queen of the seven deadlies.

06:58.328 --> 06:59.620
Wolfgang!

06:59.704 --> 07:02.415
He saw it as the ultimate gateway sin

07:02.499 --> 07:04.709
that would turn you quickly
into a sinaholic.

07:04.792 --> 07:07.879
The greatest box man in the world!

07:09.172 --> 07:13.510
But hating isn't a sin on that list.

07:13.593 --> 07:15.220
Neither is shame.

07:23.228 --> 07:24.729
[snoring softly]

07:34.447 --> 07:36.533
Come on, Dad. Time to go.

07:36.616 --> 07:40.286
I was afraid of this parade
because I wanted so badly

07:40.370 --> 07:41.829
to be a part of it.

07:41.913 --> 07:44.999
- [bird twittering]
- [insects chirring]

08:07.480 --> 08:11.901
So today,
I'm marching for that part of me

08:11.984 --> 08:14.737
that was once too afraid to march.

08:22.495 --> 08:25.206
And for all the people
who can't march...

08:26.749 --> 08:29.877
the people living lives like I did.

08:32.589 --> 08:37.093
Today, I march to remember
that I'm not just a me.

08:37.176 --> 08:39.720
I'm also a we.

08:39.804 --> 08:41.556
And we march with pride.

08:41.640 --> 08:45.184
[dance music playing]

08:47.186 --> 08:49.522
So go fuck yourself, Aquinas.

08:49.606 --> 08:51.149
Hell, yeah!

08:51.232 --> 08:54.944
[dance music continues]

09:05.330 --> 09:08.124
[shouts]

09:19.010 --> 09:20.761
- [camera clicks]
- You OK back there?

09:25.684 --> 09:26.976
[gunshot echoes]

09:28.102 --> 09:29.937
[people gasping]

09:31.105 --> 09:35.026
[singing softly]

09:41.782 --> 09:44.661
[singing in unison]

09:46.663 --> 09:50.500
- [continues singing softly]
- [heart monitor beeps steadily]

10:12.772 --> 10:15.441
- Mom, she's up.
- Oh, thank God.

10:15.525 --> 10:18.611
I was sure he was gonna
be in a coma the rest of my life.

10:20.905 --> 10:22.699
How you feeling, Michael?

10:22.782 --> 10:24.825
My name is Nomi.

10:24.909 --> 10:28.204
Oh, I'm sorry.
Your mother's been calling you Michael.

10:28.287 --> 10:30.498
What kind of name is Nomi?

10:30.582 --> 10:32.709
Have you ever heard
of anyone named Nomi?

10:32.792 --> 10:35.378
You were Michael
before you came out of me,

10:35.461 --> 10:38.130
and you will be Michael
until they put me in my grave.

10:38.214 --> 10:40.800
Mom, come on. She almost died.

10:40.883 --> 10:42.968
Serves you right.

10:44.804 --> 10:47.599
You shouldn't be riding on motorcycles.

10:47.682 --> 10:51.852
Do you know how many people a year
die on those things?

10:52.812 --> 10:54.021
Where's Amanita?

10:55.314 --> 10:56.357
She left.

10:57.858 --> 10:59.944
She wouldn't have left me.

11:00.027 --> 11:03.322
This hospital only allows family
into critical care.

11:03.406 --> 11:05.825
She is my family.

11:05.908 --> 11:08.745
Please, Michael, this isn't your blog.

11:08.828 --> 11:11.456
This is your life.

11:14.250 --> 11:15.752
I think that you should go.

11:17.002 --> 11:19.839
I'm not going anywhere.

11:19.922 --> 11:22.592
I'm your mother and I love you.

11:24.176 --> 11:26.512
It may be on my terms, but I do,

11:26.596 --> 11:30.224
so I'm not leaving here
until you talk to Dr. Metzger.

11:30.308 --> 11:34.646
You still want me to go
after he tells you what he told us...

11:37.523 --> 11:39.942
then I promise I will leave you alone.

11:41.068 --> 11:43.112
[Will] I'm not crazy.

11:43.195 --> 11:45.657
- Didn't say you were.
- Yeah, but--

11:45.740 --> 11:49.452
You didn't believe me either, not about
the woman, the building, the stash,

11:49.535 --> 11:52.037
none of it.
Maybe you'll believe a camera.

11:52.121 --> 11:54.833
Building across the street
has got a CTV.

11:54.915 --> 11:56.208
I requisitioned the file.

11:56.292 --> 11:59.003
This camera's got a perfect view
of the front and back.

11:59.086 --> 12:01.046
Anybody pulled a body out,
we'll see it.

12:02.131 --> 12:04.717
OK, this is about the time we pulled over

12:04.801 --> 12:06.511
because I thought
I saw that woman, right?

12:06.594 --> 12:09.013
Ooh, the blond ghost in her underwear.

12:09.096 --> 12:11.182
I think she visited me last night.

12:11.265 --> 12:12.725
All right, here it is.

12:16.312 --> 12:18.063
What the hell?

12:20.692 --> 12:21.942
[tapping keys]

12:23.027 --> 12:25.237
This has been erased.

12:25.321 --> 12:29.033
- Somebody erased two hours of this.
- That is weird.

12:29.784 --> 12:31.994
Man, D, something is going on here.

12:32.871 --> 12:35.581
I'll give you there's definitely
a flag on the play.

12:39.001 --> 12:42.129
Hey, yo. Check out our man here.

12:43.339 --> 12:44.883
[Diego] Uh-huh.

12:46.133 --> 12:48.469
He saw the whole thing.

12:48.553 --> 12:51.389
[Metzger] This is what a normal,
healthy brain looks like:

12:51.472 --> 12:54.517
two distinct,
well-differentiated frontal lobes.

12:54.600 --> 12:58.479
The problem begins here in
the substantia alba of the frontal lobe.

12:58.563 --> 13:01.023
These two masses
are growing into one another.

13:01.106 --> 13:03.401
You see? There's no separation.

13:03.484 --> 13:06.070
[Metzger] It's often misdiagnosed
as acute encephalitis,

13:06.153 --> 13:10.408
but it's a condition called UFLS:
undifferentiated frontal lobe syndrome.

13:11.367 --> 13:14.495
- All acronyms are scary.
- Yeah.

13:14.579 --> 13:16.915
I'll be honest with you, Nomi, is it?

13:18.040 --> 13:19.250
It's not good.

13:19.333 --> 13:21.794
There is a procedure to treat UFLS,

13:21.878 --> 13:23.755
but it requires
a very aggressive surgery

13:23.838 --> 13:25.924
where we go in
and try to cut away the growth.

13:26.006 --> 13:27.675
Oh, my God.

13:27.759 --> 13:30.803
[mother]
The surgery is also incredibly expensive.

13:30.887 --> 13:33.598
You're going to need to use our insurance.

13:33.681 --> 13:37.268
- Mom.
- These are just the facts, Teagan.

13:37.351 --> 13:39.938
And if I don't have the surgery?

13:40.020 --> 13:43.566
Without the surgery,
the tissue will continue to metastasize.

13:43.649 --> 13:48.028
Patients will begin to experience
a deterioration of mental faculties.

13:48.112 --> 13:50.406
It's common for them
to experience very intense,

13:50.489 --> 13:54.368
very real hallucinations and synesthesia
that precedes a loss of memory

13:54.452 --> 13:56.328
and a complete occlusion of identity.

13:56.412 --> 13:58.873
He told us if he didn't
operate immediately,

13:58.957 --> 14:02.835
- you could be dead within six months.
- [Teagan] Jesus Christ, Mom!

14:02.919 --> 14:07.006
You understand now, Michael?
You're going to need us.

14:07.089 --> 14:10.969
- You're going to need your family.
- Don't touch me! You are not my family!

14:11.051 --> 14:13.972
- We should go.
- This is for your own good, Michael.

14:14.054 --> 14:16.348
Don't call me that!

14:16.432 --> 14:18.643
- You're my child. I love you.
- Go!

14:18.726 --> 14:20.895
Just... [sobs] Just go.

14:29.821 --> 14:32.197
- [fans cheering]
- [overlapping chatter]

14:43.083 --> 14:45.544
[fans cheering]

14:55.220 --> 14:56.639
[cheering continues]

15:02.770 --> 15:06.983
At the premiere with one of the
rising stars in Mexico, Lito Rodriguez,

15:07.066 --> 15:13.739
who was recently voted one of the
sexiest men in the world by En Fuego.

15:13.823 --> 15:15.867
- Congratulations, Lito.
- Thank you.

15:15.950 --> 15:19.037
And the second time we've seen you
with Ms. Velasquez, isn't it?

15:19.119 --> 15:22.790
What are we to make of this?

15:22.874 --> 15:24.876
Are you guys an item now?

15:25.668 --> 15:28.462
- We're just friends.
- Good friends.

15:29.505 --> 15:31.841
OK. Good friends.
We like hanging out.

15:31.924 --> 15:33.425
He's an amazing dancer.

15:33.509 --> 15:37.013
Oh, it must be your Spanish blood, right?

15:37.096 --> 15:40.058
- His father taught flamenco.
- Oh, he was from Barcelona, wasn't he?

15:40.140 --> 15:43.185
Bilbao actually.
But he taught in Barcelona.

15:44.562 --> 15:46.105
He was a true artist.

15:46.188 --> 15:47.773
But let's be honest, Christina,

15:47.857 --> 15:51.318
when we're out on the dance floor,
nobody's looking at me.

15:51.402 --> 15:53.362
- [laughs]
- Who could take their eyes off her?

15:53.445 --> 15:55.114
[Christina] He's a keeper.

15:55.781 --> 15:59.994
And the movie is
Love Has No Boundaries But Death.

16:00.828 --> 16:05.207
[Rajan] Well, the truth is,
she never even looked at me, not once.

16:06.667 --> 16:08.669
I felt like a stalker,
waiting in the cafeteria

16:08.753 --> 16:10.295
for a chance to ask her out.

16:10.379 --> 16:12.048
[laughter]

16:12.131 --> 16:13.799
I was sure that she didn't like me.

16:14.675 --> 16:17.803
But my father taught me
that fortune favors the bold,

16:17.887 --> 16:20.431
so I decided to send her flowers
on her birthday.

16:21.140 --> 16:22.558
Lots of flowers.

16:22.641 --> 16:25.519
[woman gasps]
Oh, my God, Kala.

16:28.647 --> 16:30.274
And that got me a chance for a date.

16:30.357 --> 16:33.069
[all chuckling]

16:33.819 --> 16:36.781
Kala loves the movies,
so we went to see A Match Made by God.

16:36.864 --> 16:38.699
Of course, Auntie and Sister came along.

16:38.783 --> 16:40.200
[laughter]

16:41.410 --> 16:45.247
And when Shah Rukh Khan sang
"I See God in You,"

16:45.330 --> 16:47.207
and I saw tears in her eyes,

16:47.291 --> 16:51.087
I hoped more than anything
I've ever wanted...

16:52.088 --> 16:55.549
that one day she might
feel that way for me.

16:55.633 --> 16:58.094
- [women] Aw!
- [applause]

17:02.640 --> 17:06.644
- I told you I had a surprise for you.
- [slow guitar music plays]

17:06.727 --> 17:08.687
[applause]

17:15.194 --> 17:17.863
- [up-tempo rhythm]
- [crowd cheering]

17:19.865 --> 17:25.746
- [sings along softly in Hindi]
- [crowd clapping]

17:32.252 --> 17:34.672
[crowd whistling, cheering]

17:42.221 --> 17:45.224
[whistling, cheering]

18:02.616 --> 18:04.451
[cheering]

18:09.498 --> 18:12.001
[excited chatter]

18:13.669 --> 18:16.296
[whistling]

18:28.684 --> 18:31.353
[whistling and cheering]

18:45.784 --> 18:47.828
[song tempo quickens]

19:15.689 --> 19:18.859
- [song ends]
- [crowd cheering, whistling]

19:21.528 --> 19:24.031
[indistinct conversation]

19:26.075 --> 19:28.035
I like this man.

19:28.119 --> 19:30.704
- I really do.
- [crowd applauding]

19:32.539 --> 19:34.458
You have no idea
what's going on, right?

19:34.541 --> 19:37.878
So you just kinda have to,
like, let go and go with it.

19:37.962 --> 19:40.714
And Lito, you-- You're so good.

19:40.798 --> 19:42.341
I'll tell you the truth.

19:42.424 --> 19:45.844
Sometimes when we were shooting,
I was a little bit confused.

19:45.928 --> 19:47.763
Am I this twin here? Am I that twin?

19:47.846 --> 19:51.267
No, no, no, but you make it work.
You carry us through.

19:51.350 --> 19:56.772
I mean, there's only like one,
maybe two problems.

19:56.855 --> 19:58.232
What?

19:59.900 --> 20:01.277
[laughing]

20:02.069 --> 20:04.363
- She's horrible. Horrible.
- Come on.

20:04.488 --> 20:07.283
Don't know what's more fake,
her acting or her tits.

20:07.366 --> 20:09.076
- No, seriously--
- You're terrible.

20:09.160 --> 20:11.287
No, you don't even worry
when the ship goes down,

20:11.370 --> 20:14.790
you know she's going to float away
safely on those things. [laughs]

20:16.334 --> 20:21.297
And afterward, she came up to you
and you told her how great she was.

20:21.380 --> 20:23.507
How do you even do that?

20:25.176 --> 20:26.885
[sighs]

20:26.969 --> 20:32.766
You know, you just look them
right in the eye and you lie.

20:32.850 --> 20:34.977
It's what we do. It's called acting.

20:35.769 --> 20:37.479
Speaking of...

20:39.857 --> 20:45.196
would you like to come upstairs and...
run some lines with me?

20:45.988 --> 20:49.783
I can't. I have an early call tomorrow.

20:50.617 --> 20:52.494
- Really?
- Yeah.

20:53.871 --> 20:57.749
I am not used to men telling me no.

20:58.959 --> 21:00.711
It's kind of turning me on.

21:01.920 --> 21:03.463
- I'm sorry.
- Are you sure?

21:03.547 --> 21:05.383
- Yeah. Yeah.
- You sure? You sure?

21:05.465 --> 21:07.009
- I'll see you tomorrow.
- You sure?

21:07.092 --> 21:09.636
- Really? Are you sure?
- Yeah. Good night.

21:11.347 --> 21:12.890
Mm...

21:14.474 --> 21:17.769
[heavy panting]

21:17.853 --> 21:20.480
[moaning, panting]

21:28.447 --> 21:29.823
[gasps]

21:35.287 --> 21:37.873
[woman breathes rapidly]

21:37.956 --> 21:41.085
[crying out]

21:48.259 --> 21:49.634
[moans]

21:52.471 --> 21:54.973
[both panting]

21:55.974 --> 22:00.687
[exhales] Are you hot? Whoo.
I'm burning up.

22:01.939 --> 22:04.691
It wasn't hot
until Rajan started dancing.

22:06.818 --> 22:10.489
- He was good, wasn't he?
- He is awesome.

22:10.572 --> 22:11.823
[laughter]

22:11.907 --> 22:15.702
Trust me, if you don't marry him, I will.

22:15.786 --> 22:17.579
[laughs]

22:17.662 --> 22:20.416
He's so cute.

22:26.755 --> 22:27.798
Whoo.

22:34.805 --> 22:38.434
I think locking my keys in my car
was the best thing that's happened to me

22:38.517 --> 22:40.269
in a very long time.

22:40.352 --> 22:41.728
[chuckles]

22:43.814 --> 22:46.108
I'm hungry.

22:49.027 --> 22:50.779
I can make something.

22:50.862 --> 22:53.824
No, I have a real craving.

22:55.575 --> 22:56.952
For what?

22:58.287 --> 22:59.871
Indian food.

23:00.664 --> 23:02.833
Sanyam, sir, the food was unbelievable.

23:02.916 --> 23:04.793
- Really, everybody was blown away.
- [woman] Yes.

23:04.876 --> 23:07.671
- Thank you. Thank you.
- Yes, it was very good.

23:07.754 --> 23:10.549
Even though I don't much like
Indian food, but it was good.

23:10.632 --> 23:13.218
I'm more than willing
to help with the wedding if--

23:13.302 --> 23:15.053
Oh, no, no. That won't be necessary.

23:15.137 --> 23:18.932
We're bringing in finest chefs
from Europe and Asia. We are good.

23:19.016 --> 23:22.561
They say the only thing people
remember about a wedding is the food.

23:22.644 --> 23:24.313
- Yes.
- Well, if it's going to be as good

23:24.396 --> 23:27.941
as yours was tonight, then the wedding
is definitely going to be unforgettable.

23:28.025 --> 23:30.152
What is unforgettable was your song.

23:30.235 --> 23:32.696
Yes, it was the highlight
of the evening.

23:32.779 --> 23:33.947
Thank you, Auntie.

23:37.284 --> 23:38.618
Did you like it?

23:38.702 --> 23:41.746
I did, very much. [giggles]

23:42.873 --> 23:46.043
Sir, is it all right if I say good night?

23:46.126 --> 23:48.420
Yes, yes. Go on. Yes.

23:50.005 --> 23:51.298
